Someone asked what I accomplished in 2023 & I had to really think about it. 

Because I have been doing so much internal work in the past 4 years, it’s hard to pinpoint the tangible things society deems valuable.

And I don’t want to tell you how I grew my IG or TikTok or YouTube or Likee or Bigo… Because it isn’t real. Once you understand social media like I do, you will know without a doubt how easy it is to have hundreds of thousands or even millions of followers without actually bringing much value to the world or being a decent human being.

Don’t get me wrong 😑 I love social media more than anything; and marketing, when it is done with ethics & morals in mind, is absolute magic ♥️ I have been living and breathing social media marketing these past 4 years.

So don’t let the bullies make you feel small with their fake accomplishments & have faith in your kind and generous self. Trust me the people who make it big, like Elon Musk or Jeff Bezos, made it because they solved a problem on a very large scale that has helped humanity immensely, not because they bragged on social media about some little following they have (that they purchased from a marketing agency for a LOT of money or did some shady stuff for it).

The other thing I will not tell you is how I got married or had kids, because I haven’t 🤭 Staying true to yourself and not settling is an accomplishment in itself. I am not talking about victims or women who didn’t know better due to youth/circumstances. But those who use their children as a source of emotional energy and financial support. I am getting married to my one and only with absolutely pure intentions. No trauma bonding for me, no thank you. No playing victim for me, no thank you. My kids deserve the best.

What I did do in late 2023 is get a pretty bad cold, after successfully avoiding Covid (no vaccines, no thank you) & not having the flu for over 4 years. In 2018 started water fasting, went up to 19 days on water, realised I was no longer getting much health results, so I started dry fasting and went up to 6 days 9 hours no food, no water, then I hit a wall…

IG says my caption is too long so ‘to be continued’ in tomorrow’s post ☺️✌🏻✨

The rest of yesterday’s IG post story I’ll share with you in an upcoming YouTube video 🤭 Not trying to be mysterious, just that Instagram will get mad at me again if I keep writing these long AF posts 😅🫶🏻🧸 Tomorrow is the first new moon of our calendar year, let’s release all the trauma of 2023 & keep the lessons for 2024. Everything you focus on this year, will serve you long term, so choose wisely 👏🏻♥️ ∞ ❧ #newyearnewme #newyearnewus ☙
